<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="ida9898a94-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2000—<ref href="/us/pl/106/398">Pub. L. 106–398</ref> renumbered <ref href="/us/usc/t10/s2548">section 2548 of this title</ref> as this section.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="ida9898a95-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="ida9898a96-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p><ref href="/us/pl/101/189/dA/tIII/s329/b">Pub. L. 101–189, div. A, title III, § 329(b)</ref>, <date date="1989-11-29">Nov. 29, 1989</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/103/1417">103 Stat. 1417</ref>, provided that: <quotedContent origin="/us/pl/101/189/dA/tIII/s329/b">“Section 2548 [now 2558] of title 10, United States Code, as added by subsection (a), shall take effect on the date of the enactment of this Act [<date date="1989-11-29">Nov. 29, 1989</date>].”</quotedContent>
</p>
</note>
</notes>
